The paper deals with interference management in a network of macrocells and femtocells, which is a problem related to network communication and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes policies for optimizing network performance, which involves information theory and optimization techniques, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper also mentions scheduling and optimization algorithms, which could fall under cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper proposes a decentralized implementation of the policies, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
